Which ever programming language one use, one question that always comes is printing a given pattern.
These are easy once you know the basics and 3 simple rules.

Generally printing a pattern consists of printing numbers, alphabets or a character in the form of rows and columns.
This is very easy once you know how you can manipulate the loops on your wish

I Identify the number of rows to be printed.
II Identify how many columns are required to be printed in i'th row.
III Find out what has to be printed.
